{
  "text": "The first prospectively validated risk assessment tool for febrile neutropenic patients was developed by Talcott et al. [CITATION_1] . It consisted in a clinical model involving 4 categories of patients at risk whose risk status is clinically assessable within 24 h of admission: preexisting inpatients, outpatients with severe comorbidity, outpatients with progressing neoplasia, and all others. Multiple complications were more frequent among preexisting inpatients; overall mortality was 8%, with a 14% rate for outpatients with progressing neoplasia.",
